<section class='faq'>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="column column--double">
      <h2>FAQs</h2>
      <p class="question">Who can attend?</p>
      <p class="answer"> Any high school student may apply, but only accepted students may attend. </p>
      
      <p class="question">When/where is Tech Retreat happening?</p>
      <p class="answer">Tech Retreat will run on the weekend of July 9-10 at St. Paul’s University College, which is located at Canada’s most
innovative school—The University of Waterloo.</p>
        
      <p class="question">How much does this cost?</p>
      <p class="answer">Nothing! It's absolutely free. Food will also be provided.</p>
      
      <p class="question">What food is provided?</p>
      <p class="answer">Saturday's lunch and dinner along with Sunday's breakfast and lunch will be provided. Also, snacks will be available throughout the weekend.</p>

      <p class="question">What about overnight lodging?</p>
      <p class="answer">We have a limited amount of dorm style rooms available if you're feeling tired.</p>

      <p class="question">What should I bring?</p>
      <p class="answer">A laptop and charger, reusable water bottle, government photo ID (if you're signing out hardware), and your brilliant mind. Feel free to bring a sleeping bag, toothbrush, and other basic amenities for this overnight event.</p>

      <p class="question">Is there a code of conduct?</p>
      <p class="answer">Yes, <a href="code.html" alt="Code of conduct">check it out!</a></p>
    </div>
